# merge fixture: an input that is NOT internally time-sorted, for a 2-file
# merge (the merge path only runs for 2+ inputs). IRIG records at 200us, 400us,
# 150us — the third record steps backward in time relative to the second
# (within-file monotonicity violation, L2-MRG-006). Paired with merge-a.hex
# (100us, 300us). Lenient: WARN once + emit all rows (the 150us row sorts out
# last, after 400us). Strict (--strict): exit 1 before completing.

